argin-left:30px;">Applicable to all records maintained for the quality management system. </p>                <h2>3.	RESPONSIBILITY :  </h2>                <p style="margin-left:30px;">                    MR and concerned department heads are responsible to implement & maintain this procedure.                </p>                <h2>                    4.	PROCEDURE   :                </h2>                <h3 style="margin-left:30px;">                    4.1	IDENTIFICATION &nbsp; & RETENTION TIME OF RECORDS :                </h3>                <h5 style="margin-left:50px;">4.1.1</h5>                <p style="margin-left:70px;">                    MR shall maintain the list of records in doc. no. D MR 04 considering the effective operation of the quality management system.                    All records are identified by unique numbering system as per procedure PCMR04. MR shall define the retention period of the record in doc.                    no. D MR 04 considering the evaluation requirements. MR shall issue the list of records to concerned person for maintaining & controlling                    these records.                </p>                <h3 style="margin-left:30px;">4.2	RETRIEVAL OF RECORD :</h3>                <h5 style="margin-left:50px;">4.2.1</h5>                <p style="margin-left:70px;">                    Concerned department head shall maintain proper indexing and filing of records so that it can be easily retrieved whenever required.                    The method of indexing shall be defined in list of records, doc. no. D MR 04.                </p>                <h3 style="margin-left:30px;">4.3	STORAGE &nbsp; & PROTECTION &nbsp; OF RECORDS :</h3>                <h5 style="margin-left:50px;">                    4.3.1                </h5>                <p style="margin-left:70px;">                    Records are stored in cabinet or racks at the regular location. All records are retained up to the defined retention period.                    All records shall be stored and retained in such a way that they are remaining legible and facilitates a suitable environment to prevent                    damage or deterioration and to prevent loss.                </p>                <h3 style="margin-left:30px;">4.4 	DISPOSITION OF RECORDS :</h3>                <h5 style="margin-left:50px;">                    4.4.1                </h5>                <p style="margin-left:70px;">                    After completion of retention time, all the records shall be destroyed through burning or shredding or it can be used as rough pad.                    Where agreed contractually, records shall be made available for evaluation by the customer or customer’s representative for an                    agreed period                </p>                <h2>                    Reference :                </h2>                <ol style="margin-left:30px;">                    <li> List of Records				: D MR 04</li>                    <li>Procedure for control of documents	: PC MR 03</li>                </ol>                <h2>Records : 	Nil</h2>                <table>                    <tr>                        <th colspan="3" width="35%">Prepared By</th>                        <th colspan="3" width="35%">Approved By</th>                        <th rowspan="3"></th>                    </tr>                    <tr>                        <td colspan="3" style="height:5vh" width="35%"></td>                        <td colspan="3" style="height:5vh" width="35%"></td>                    </tr>                    <tr>                        <th colspan="3" width="35%">MR</th>                        <th colspan="3" width="35%">PARTNER</th>                    </tr>                </table>            </div>        </div>    </div>    <script>                document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {            document.getElementById("downloadPdf").addEventListener("click", () => {                const { jsPDF } = window.jspdf;                const pdf = new jsPDF("p", "mm", "a4");                // Get elements to hide                const btn = document.getElementById("downloadPdf");                const logo = document.getElementById("top-logo");                // Temporarily hide elements                if (btn) btn.style.display = "none";                if (logo) logo.style.display = "none";                html2canvas(document.getElementById("pdf-content")).then(canvas => {                    const imgData = canvas.toDataURL("image/png");                    const imgWidth = 190; // A4 width in mm                    const imgHeight = (canvas.height * imgWidth) / canvas.width;                    pdf.addImage(imgData, "PNG", 10, 10, imgWidth, imgHeight);                    pdf.save("PCMR04.pdf");                    // Restore elements after PDF is generated                    if (btn) btn.style.display = "block";                    if (logo) logo.style.display = "block";                });            });        });    </script>    <!-- Include jsPDF and html2canvas -->    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/html2canvas/1.4.1/html2canvas.min.js"></script>    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/jspdf/2.5.1/jspdf.umd.min.js"></script></body></html>